Transaction:
---------------
a transaction is a sequence of one or more sql operations executed as a single logical unitofwork. it ensure either all operations are completely successfully or then are applied to the database.


Interview
--------------
A transaction is a logical unit of work consisting one or more sql statements that fallows the ACID properites to maintain data integrity and consistency

ACID properties
------------------
Atomicity: either all operations happen or none happen.
consistency: the database remains in a valid state before and after the transaction.
Isolated: concurrent transactions do not interface with each other.
Durability: once committed changes are permanent even if the  system crashes

